    "narrative": "Our offensive outlook for April 23rd is largely dictated by a daunting matchup against Glasnow, who anchors a series of low-ceiling projections across our core. **Geraldo Perdomo** stands out as our clear offensive anchor today, carrying an elite 69.48 score into his contest against Martin. His projection is bolstered by a massive 17% boost from the opposing SP\u2019s high xERA and the inherent value of his leadoff spot, which maximizes his exposure to potential scoring opportunities. While **Bryson Stott** (62.16) is our only other \"Strong\" play, he earns his keep against Cabrera due to favorable wind conditions and a solid platoon split, providing necessary stability while the rest of the lineup grinds through tougher assignments.\n\nThe decision to bench our deeper roster stems from today\u2019s scheduling congestion; with **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, **Cal Raleigh**, **Lawrence Butler**, and **Yainer Diaz** all observing league-wide off-days, our bench utility is effectively non-existent. Among the active players, **Matt Chapman** (57.06) remains a difficult start against a pitcher as dominant as Glasnow, though he is elevated by the \"slow delivery\" metric, which we believe creates high-probability theft windows\u2014a priority given the extreme scarcity of stolen bases in our league format. Similarly, **Jung Hoo Lee** (53.32) remains in the lineup despite the tough opponent, as his dynamic platoon profile provides a higher floor than our late-order options like **Drew Gilbert** (44.84) or **Wenceel Perez** (44.59), both of whom are suppressed by suboptimal batting order positions. \n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the Glasnow-heavy slate; the volatility introduced by his elite skill set poses a significant risk of sub-40 efficiency across our outfield. While **Gleyber Torres** (51.36) faces a more manageable matchup against Sproat, his score is currently dampened by a negative platoon adjustment, making him a candidate for mid-game substitution should early-inning adjustments fail to materialize. With no reinforcements coming from the bench until tomorrow, we are effectively locked into this configuration, trusting that the stolen base potential in the middle of our order can mitigate the high probability of suppressed power numbers against the Glasnow gauntlet.",
